<br>
1) If you get the NEW PoP rains spells, Sunstorm, Maelstrom Of Thunder, please note the INITIAL RESIST rates you get, but then keep using spells and compare resists rates at start and end.<br>
<br>
Again testing a NEW rain spell I got FAR higher resists rates within first 15 or so casts than I did later. Should really have logged this but seems correlation, as I've said before, between a new spell and its number of uses compared to resists, that is, a NEW spell has horrible resist rates until this been used a while. <br>
Doubt me if you will but with rain spells I sure notice this.<br>
Also Sunstorm is pretty good for giving partial, rather than total resists.<br>
<br>
2) It maybe just me but...was in PoV, I'm lvl 63, I had no Brilliacne of Ro effects that may effect casting lvl, just KEI, and SCM3...after na hour or so nuking with Sunstorm, who's initial resists rates SUCKED HUGELY, resists fell dramatically.<br>
I found this spell may get partials now but far less full resists than previosuly  and is actually PRETTY DARN GOOD! <br>
<br>
I dont have enough FT and am not Evocation specialist, but I suspect if you DO have those things, chaining SUnstorm with Maesltrom of THunder, or Malestrom Of Electricity/Sirocco is a very good way of dealing with PoP mobs.<br>
<br>
Why is it good?<br>
PoP mobs must die *FAST!* They simply hit too damn hard to Piddle around with. Faster they die the better, far more so than any other time in EQ since the early days, ie nukage is IMPORTANT.<br>
Rains draw low aggro. You can chain 2 rains back to back, you can drop 6k of damage on a mob with rains, PDQ.<br>
you drop 3 Firebolts of Tallon on a mob generally you get CHEWED (well I do anyway :&gt;), but I wasnt drawing the same aggro chaining rains.<br>
<br>
Of course the usual caveats with rains apply: bad around mezzedmobs, beware of &quot;through-wall aggro&quot;, z axis aggro and resist rates are still worse than DDs, but...the group I was with noticed the difference in kill speeds. Got my wiz pal to chain rains to after a bit, mobs were *scythed*! He was sitll getting iffy resist rates, so guess two levels I had more really make difference for resists (though wiz DDs get way less resisted than my by comparison, and mobs we were fighting were close to or were even con to the wizard).<br>
<br>
To get best effect you'd want mobs debuffed, the Malosini pendant from VT, used as mob is inc, woudl probably help a great deal if you try this.<br>
<br>
